1 consultation with the Cabinet for Economic Development, shall conduct a thorough
2 economic feasibility analysis on any major energy-using component of at least three
3 million (3,000,000) BTU's per hour heat input and shall issue a certificate of
4 economic feasibility prior to the Finance and Administration Cabinet's purchasing
5 or retrofitting any such component that utilizes any fuel other than coal. The
6 economic feasibility analysis shall consist of life-cycle cost comparisons of a
7 component that would utilize coal and one(s) that would utilize any fuel other than
8 coal. For the analysis, the Finance and Administration Cabinet shall provide
9 detailed estimates of equipment purchase price, installation cost, annual operation
10 and maintenance costs, and usage patterns of energy-using components.
