21 even if the reduced price requires the purchase of a specified quantity of units
22 different from the quantity stated in the original price agreement. Price reductions
23 under this subsection shall not be considered to permanently alter the price of the
24 supplies or equipment under the price agreement with the Commonwealth, except
25 where the price reductions are to be made permanent under the express terms of the
26 price agreement and where the purchasing agency which solicited the price
27 agreement determines that the enforcement of those terms serves the best interest of
